snippet: An unusual approach by Judge Barbara B. Crabb of Federal District Court has pitted county clerks against the Wisconsin attorney general.
abstract: Legal confusion has followed federal Judge Barabara B Crabb's unusual approach in striking down Wisconsin's ban on same-sex marriage; Crabb neglected to issue official injunction ordering state to comply, meaning decision is not final; situation has prevented higher courts from issuing stay and has pitted county clerks against Wisconsin's Republican attorney general, J B Van Hollen, over whether marriage licenses can or cannot be granted in interim.
lead_paragraph: An unusual approach by Judge Barbara B. Crabb of Federal District Court has pitted county clerks against the Wisconsin attorney general.

headline.main: Legal Confusion Follows Federal Judge’s Ruling on Same-Sex Marriage in Wisconsin
